The inflow controls enhancements touch the whole definition of how we have inflow controls set up in the model. Currently there is little if any help and barely any diagnostics. The process is totally non-visual, except inside XP-SWMM.
The goals are: * avoid rebuilding the model when you add an inflow control * Existing tool are not consistent and are exclusive; desire a single uniform framework.
The current methods involve field inspections for feasability. A blanket "let there be controls" has proven to overstate the control benefits.
